nodes.bodyText:
In Scala you can do:
val dequeued = {
  val count = eventQueueTimeHist.count()
  if (count != 0) {
    val event = queue.poll(..., ...)
    if (event == null) {
      eventQueueTimeHist.clear()
      queue.take()
    } else {
      event
    }
  } else {
    queue.take()
  }
}
We can probably move this code to a private method.

